The paper discusses the role of artificial agents in manipulating human cognitive biases and the need for developing benevolent artificial agents to prevent and mitigate cognitive distortions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI). The paper also touches upon the topic of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the context of developing more objective artificial agents. Finally, the paper discusses the subjective nature of human causal cognition, which could be related to the sub-category of Cybernetics (cs.CY).
